$ choice.exe

`choice.exe` allow a → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/batch-files[`cmd.exe` batch file] to present a list of options from which a user can choose from.
-
The number of the chosen item is then stored in → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/variables/errorlevel[`%errorlevel%`] and different actions can be taken using
an → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/commands/if[`if` statement].

gh|about-cmd.exe|/batch-files/choose.bat||

sa:
  The `/t` option is also used in → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/timeout_exe[`timout.exe`] for time out.
